---
description: CSS / Mantine styling for React
globs: "**/*.tsx,**/*.css.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- DO NOT USE TAILWIND.
- This project uses Mantine as a component library (proxied from `app/frontend/components`).
- CSS is written using CSS modules with Linaria in separate files with a `css.ts` extension, colocated with the component.
- CSS is imported into React components using `import * as classes from "./Component.css"`. Always use `import clsx from "clsx"` and pass every `className` through `clsx(...)`, even when there is only one class.
- Mantine CSS variables are exported using Mantine's `themeToVars`. Use them via `vars` from `@/lib`.
- Each `css.ts` file starts with:
  `import { css } from "@linaria/core"`
  `import { vars } from "@/lib"`
- Styles in `css.ts` files are built using the `css` function from Linaria with string template literals.
